					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Irene Zabytko</h4>
												<p>Irene Zabytko is the Ukrainian-American author of <em>The Sky Unwashed</em>, a novel set against the backdrop of the Chornobyl explosion, and <em>When Luba Leaves Home: Stories</em>, a set of interrelated short stories based on a Ukrainian neighborhood in Chicago. Her short stories have appeared in numerous journals and anthologies and her nonfiction has appeared in the <em>New York Times Book Review</em>, the <em>Chicago Tribune Sunday Magazine</em>, and elsewhere. She received a Fulbright U.S. Scholar award in Ukraine for an upcoming novel based on the life of Nikolai Gogol. She holds a BA and an MFA in Creative Writing from Vermont College.</p>
